msgid ""
"When first inserting a USB drive, a :guilabel:`New Device` message will "
"appear in the system tray. Click the :guilabel:`Mount Tray` icon, then "
":guilabel:`Mount` for the device. Mount Tray will try to determine the "
"filesystem on the device and then to mount it. If it is not sure, a pop-up "
"menu will prompt to select the correct filesystem. A list of supported "
"filesystems can be found in :ref:`filesys support`. Once mounted, "
":guilabel:`Mount` changes to :guilabel:`Unmount`, and if the device contains"
" files, an indicator of the drive's used capacity and a button to "
":guilabel:`Browse` the contents of the device will be added. An example is "
"shown in :numref:`Figure %s <mount2>`."
msgstr ""

